t%20was%20a%20huge%20success%20and%20is%20still%20celebrated%20for%20its%20emotional%20depth%20and%20memorable%20dialogues.%20The%20film's%20soundtrack%20also%20played%20a%20significant%20role%20in%20its%20success.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fdeleted-scene-of-abhishek-bachchan-fighting-with-kareena-kapoor-in-kabhi-khushi-kabhie-gham-goes-viral%2Farticleshow%2F104614433.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20real%20science%20behind%20the%20mysterious%20'Devil%20Comet'%20that's%20larger%20than%20Mount%20Everest%20and%20erupting%20for%20reasons%20scientists%20don't%20fully%20understand%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221426%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22black%20and%20white%20image%20of%20sky%20full%20of%20stars%2C%20with%20brighter%2C%20fuzzy%20constellation%20at%20center%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6533f36796908fd7cdb49e2a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221005%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20solid%20body%20of%2012P%2FPons-Brooks%20is%20hidden%20underneath%20all%20the%20dust%20and%20gas%20in%20the%20central%20blob%20in%20the%20center%20of%20the%20image%2C%20taken%20at%20the%204.3-meter%20Lowell%20Discovery%20Telescope.%20T%20expanding%20ejecta%20from%20the%20late-July%20outburst%20can%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20faint%20two-tailed%20or%20two-horned%20structure%20at%20larger%20distances%20from%20the%20blob.%3Cp%3EDr.%20Teddy%20Kareta%2FLowell%20Observatory%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%2012P%2FPons-Brooks%20comet%20is%20passing%20by%20Earth%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20the%2021st%20century.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20is%20larger%20than%20typical%20comets%20and%20has%20been%20dubbed%20the%20%26quot%3BDevil%20Comet%26quot%3B%20for%20appearing%20to%20have%20horns.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BWe%20know%20it's%20big.%20We%20know%20it's%20an%20outlier.%20We%20know%20it's%20rare%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20researcher%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20so-called%20%26quot%3BDevil%20Comet%26quot%3B%20is%20barreling%20past%20Earth%20and%20exploding%20on%20its%20way%20around%20the%20sun%2C%20but%20a%20researcher%20who%20studies%20such%20phenomenon%20told%20Insider%20that%20while%20the%20comet%20is%20large%20and%20unusual%2C%20its%20menacing%20name%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%20reference%20to%20the%20appearance%20of%20horns%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0does%20not%20mean%20it%20poses%20any%20threat%20to%20the%20third%20planet%20from%20the%20sun.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKnown%20to%20scientists%20as%2012P%2FPons-Brooks%2C%20the%20comet%20last%20made%20an%20appearance%20in%20Earth's%20skies%20more%20than%2070%20years%20ago.%20Judging%20by%20its%20brightness%2C%20astronomers%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fiopscience.iop.org%2Farticle%2F10.3847%2F2515-5172%2Faba2d1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eestimated%20that%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20solid%20part%20of%20the%20comet%2C%20or%20its%20nucleus%2C%20is%20about%2012.4%20miles%20across%20%E2%80%94%20roughly%20twice%20the%20size%20of%20Mount%20Everest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETypically%2C%20comets%20are%20between%200.6%20and%201.8%20miles%20wide%2C%20according%20to%20Teddy%20Kareta%2C%20a%20postdoctoral%20researcher%20at%20Lowell%20Observatory%20in%20Flagstaff%2C%20Arizona.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20know%20it's%20big.%20We%20know%20it's%20an%20outlier.%20We%20know%20it's%20rare%2C%26quot%3B%20Kareta%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20know%20it%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20most%20visible%20next%20spring%2C%20but%20not%20because%20it's%20barreling%20toward%20Earth%20in%20another%20extinction-level%20event.%20In%20fact%2C%20Kareta%20said%2C%20at%20its%20closest%20the%20comet%20will%20still%20be%20about%20one-and-half%20astronomical%20units%20away%2C%20or%20put%20another%20away%3A%20even%20further%20from%20Earth%20than%20the%20sun.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20might%20be%20bright%20enough%20that%20you%20can%20see%20with%20your%20naked%20eye%20or%20with%20binoculars%2C%20but%20that's%20not%20because%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20super%20close%2C%26quot%3B%20Kareta%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20because%20it's%20just%20generally%20very%20bright.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20the%20comet%20is%20both%20bright%20and%20highly%20unusual.%20Its%20%26quot%3Bhorns%26quot%3B%20are%20actually%20tails%20of%20gas%20and%20dust%20formed%20by%20an%20odd%20series%20of%20explosive%20outbursts%20that%20scientists%20still%20do%20not%20understand.%20Two%20such%20outbursts%20have%20been%20witnessed%20this%20year%3A%20first%20in%20July%2C%20then%20earlier%20this%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20%26quot%3Boutburst%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Kareta%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Bwhere%20comets%20suddenly%20get%20much%20more%20active%2C%26quot%3B%20throwing%20off%20tons%20of%20gas%20and%20dust%20in%20a%20short%20period%20of%20time.%20When%20this%20happens%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20comet%20brightens%20really%20rapidly%20and%20then%20sort%20of%20fades%20back%20to%20the%20brightness%20it%20had%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20in%20Pons-Brooks%2C%20these%20are%20really%2C%20really%20bright%20%E2%80%94%20really%2C%20really%20large%20outbursts.%20And%20this%20is%20what%20makes%20this%20comet%20so%20interesting%20to%20scientists.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20outbursts%20have%20been%20particularly%20interesting%20due%20to%20their%20frequency%20and%20where%20they%20occurred.%20One%20theory%20is%20that%20comets%20contain%20forms%20of%20ice%20that%2C%20when%20exposed%20for%20the%20first%20time%20to%20heat%20from%20the%20sun%2C%20cause%20volatile%20explosions.%20But%20those%20explosions%20have%20typically%20been%20observed%20closer%20to%20the%20sun%2C%20and%20not%20often.%20According%20to%20Kareta%2C%20%26quot%3Bit%20might%20happen%20twice%20in%20five%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Pons-Brooks%20comet%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20is%20exploding%20relatively%20often%20and%2C%20confoundingly%2C%20far%20away%20from%20the%20sun.%20Right%20now%2C%20it's%20further%20off%20than%20Mars%2C%20Kareta%20noted%2C%20where%20%26quot%3Bit's%20just%20not%20that%20warm.%26quot%3B%20That%20raises%20the%20question%3A%20%26quot%3BWhere's%20the%20energy%20coming%20from%20that%20powers%20these%20kinds%20of%20large%20outbursts%3F%20And%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20can%20apparently%20do%20so%20many%2C%20so%20often%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20comet%20is%20expected%20to%20reach%20peak%20brightness%20in%20mid-April%202024%20as%20it%20continues%20on%20its%2071.2-year%20journey%20around%20the%20sun.%20Astronomers%2C%20professional%20or%20otherwise%2C%20are%20looking%20forward%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20are%20really%20excited%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Kareta%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdevil-comet-excites-scientists-as-it-passes-through-solar-system-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697909340000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6533f38bbe9edfa8eda6cd61%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdevil-comet-excites-scientists-as-it-passes-through-solar-system-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%2012P%2FPons-Brooks%20comet%20is%20passing%20by%20Earth%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20the%2021st%20century.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jorwig%40businessinsider.com%20(Jessica%20Orwig%2CCharles%20R.%20Davis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A123%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdevil-comet-excites-scientists-as-it-passes-through-solar-system-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bobby%20Charlton%2C%20the%20Manchester%20United%20and%20England%20soccer%20great%2C%20dies%20at%2086%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%