lting%20all%20state%20and%20union%20territories%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20and%20other%20stakeholders.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAsking%20all%20stakeholders%20to%20therefore%20%E2%80%9Cstrictly%20adhere%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20counselling%20session%20fixed%20by%20the%20NMC%20for%20the%20academic%20session%20of%202023-24%20for%20the%20undergraduate%20MBBS%20course%2C%20the%20notification%20issued%20by%20Shambhu%20Sharan%20Kumar%2C%20director%20of%20undergraduate%20medical%20education%20board%2C%20said%20those%20who%20were%20accommodated%20after%20the%20September%2030%20deadline%20would%20be%20declared%20invalid%20and%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20students%20admitted%2C%20if%20any%2C%20shall%20be%20discharged%20immediately%E2%80%9D.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKumar%20also%20underlined%20that%20in%202019%2C%20the%20SC%20had%20stated%20that%20seats%20lying%20vacant%20would%20not%20be%20a%20%E2%80%9Cjustifiable%20reason%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20institutes%20to%20extend%20the%20cut-off%20date%20or%20allow%20admissions%20beyond%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20such%20students%20were%20asked%20to%20go%2C%20hundreds%20of%20MBBS%20seats%20would%20remain%20vacant%20across%20the%20country%2C%20unless%20the%20SC%20further%20extends%20the%20September%2030%20deadline.%20Most%20of%20the%20students%20who%20are%20to%20lose%20their%20admission%20had%20responded%20to%20the%20advertisements%20put%20out%20by%20medical%20colleges%20seeking%20admission.%20According%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fchennai%2F600-mbbs-students-to-lose-seats-in-nmc-crackdown%2Farticleshow%2F104592879.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ETimes%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20report%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Bihar%20Combined%20Entrance%20Competitive%20Examination%20Board%20had%20advertised%20on%20October%209%20inviting%20applications%20for%20a%20stray%20vacancy%20round.%E2%80%9D%20The%20report%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9COfficials%20in%20Bengal%20said%20the%20number%20of%20vacant%20seats%20was%20still%20being%20compiled.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAdmission%20to%20more%20than%20350%20MBBS%20seats%20in%20Puducherry%20was%20done%20after%20September%2030%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20added.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20news%20report%20also%20underlined%20that%20several%20students%20had%20left%20seats%20in%20others%20streams%20to%20join%20the%20MBBS%20course%20and%20would%20now%20be%20staring%20at%20losing%20an%20academic%20year.%20The%20report%20said%20while%20more%20than%20600%20students%20are%20likely%20to%20lose%20their%20admission%20for%20violation%20of%20the%20NMC%20guidelines%20by%20the%20institutes%2C%20mismanagement%20of%20the%20counselling%20process%20%E2%80%9Cwill%20result%20in%20more%20than%202000%20MBBS%20seats%20across%20the%20country%20going%20waste.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20NMC%20had%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Fedugraph%2Fnews%2Fnmc-issues-warning-mbbs-admissions-post-september-30-deemed-invalid%2Fcid%2F1974639%5C%22%3Eissued%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20deadline%20of%20October%2020%2C%202023%2C%20for%20all%20medical%20colleges%20to%20provide%20details%20of%20the%20first-year%20MBBS%20admissions%20for%20the%202023-24%20academic%20year.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697885906000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F21162624%2F2-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fnational-medical-commission-mbbs-students-deadline%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20notification%20issued%20by%20Shambhu%20Sharan%20Kumar%2C%20director%20of%20undergraduate%20medical%20education%20board%2C%20said%20those%20who%20were%20accommodated%20after%20the%20September%2030%20deadline%20would%20be%20declared%20'invalid.'%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fnational-medical-commission-mbbs-students-deadline%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Pakistan's%20Former%20PM%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20Returns%20Home%20from%20Exile%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F21155724%2FDeath_anniversary_of_Fazil_Rahoo-e1697884729243.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EPakistan%E2%80%99s%20former%20prime%20minister%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20returned%20to%20the%20country%20on%20Saturday%2C%20after%20four%20years%20of%20self-imposed%20exile%20in%20London%2C%20to%20restart%20his%20political%20journey%20ahead%20of%20the%20general%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESharif%E2%80%99s%20return%20comes%20as%20the%20country%20struggles%20with%20high%20inflation%20and%20other%20deep-seated%20issues.%20The%20economic%20crisis%20has%20intensified%20since%20his%20brother%20Shehbaz%20Sharif%20took%20power%2016%20months%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20a%20time%20for%20hope%20and%20celebration.%20His%20return%20bodes%20well%20for%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20economy%20and%20its%20people%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Khawaja%20Muhammad%20Asif%2C%20a%20senior%20leader%20of%20Sharif%E2%80%99s%20Pakistan%20Muslim%20League-Nawaz%20(PML-N)%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20thrice-elected%20prime%20minister%20was%20traveling%20on%20a%20chartered-plane%20from%20Dubai%20along%20with%20an%20entourage%20of%20194%20people%20including%20party%20members%20and%20journalists%2C%20according%20to%20party%20sources.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESharif%20landed%20in%20Islamabad%20and%20was%20set%20to%20travel%20to%20his%20stronghold%2C%20Lahore%2C%20where%20he%20is%20expected%20to%20address%20a%20rally%20of%20supporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTens%20of%20thousands%20of%20people%20have%20already%20reached%20Lahore%20to%20welcome%20Sharif%2C%E2%80%9D%20Muhammad%20Mehdi%2C%20a%20close%20aide%20to%20Sharif%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20a%20million%20supporters%20are%20expected%20to%20attend%20the%20rally%2C%20according%20to%20Mehdi.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChallenges%20lying%20ahead%20of%20Nawaz%20Sharif%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESharif%20was%20ousted%20in%202017%2C%20during%20his%20third%20stint%20as%20the%20prime%20minister%20of%20Pakistan%20and%20in%202018%20was%20sentenced%20to%20a%20seven-year%20prison%20term%20on%20multiple%20charges%20of%20corruption.%20In%202019%2C%20he%20was%20released%20on%20bail%20due%20to%20his%20health%20problems%20and%20allowed%20to%20seek%20out%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20week%2C%20Sharif%20was%20granted%20a%20protective%20bail%20which%20barred%20his%20arrest%20and%20hence%20allowing%20him%20to%20come%20back%20from%20self-exile.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20Sharif%20is%20returning%20ahead%20of%20the%20general%20elections%2C%20he%20is%20barred%20from%20running%20for%20office%20again%20due%20to%20the%20court%20rulings%20against%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHis%20legal%20team%2C%20however%2C%20says%20the%20Pakistani%20leader%20intends%20to%20make%20a%20court%20appeal.%20Party%20members%20say%20that%20he%20is%20vying%20to%20gain%20popularity%20and%20become%20prime%20minister%20for%20a%20fourth%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20Sharif%2C%20the%20biggest%20challenge%20lies%20in%20regaining%20the%20confidence%20of%20the%20public%20competing%20against%20his%20fiercely%20popular%20political%20rival%2C%20Imran%20Khan.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSharif%E2%80%99s%20key%20challenge%20is%20first%20to%20establish%20himself%20and%20his%20party%20as%20viable%20options%20to%20replace%20Imran%20Khan%2C%20who%20is%20already%20popular%2C%20and%20secondly%20to%20turn%20around%20the%20economy%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20political%20analyst%20Ayesha%20Siddiqa.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20first%20appeared%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fpakistans-former-pm-nawaz-sharif-returns-home-from-exile%2Fa-67171220%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697884825000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F21155724%2FDeath_anniversary_of_Fazil_Rahoo-e1697884729243.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fpakistans-former-pm-nawaz-sharif-returns-home-from-exile%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sharif%20is%20expected%20hold%20a%20large%20rally%20in%20Lahore.%20The%20nation%20is%20facing%20a%20deep%20economic%20crisis%20under%20the%20current%20government%20led%20by%20Sharif's%20brother.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fpakistans-former-pm-nawaz-sharif-returns-home-from-exile%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20the%20%E2%80%98Ayodhya%20Ram%20Temple%E2%80%99%20Pandal%20Cannot%20Be%20a%20Centrepiece%20of%20Kolkata's%20Durga%20Puja%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F18161334%2FScreenshot-2023-10-18-at-4.13.24%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Durga%20Puja%20in%20Kolkata%20is%20known%20for%20its%20syncretism.%20Here%2C%20celebrations%20cross%20religious%20and%20communal%20boundaries%2C%20and%20people%2C%20irrespective%20of%20their%20religions%2C%20visit%20the%20puja%20pandals%20(decorated%20pavilions)%20dotting%20the%20city%2C%20something%20which%20we%2C%20the%20natives%20of%20the%20city%2C%20are%20proud%20of.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEven%20in%20these%20times%20of%20commercialisation%20of%20the%20festival%2C%20many%20of%20the%20so-called%20%E2%80%9Ctheme%E2%80%9D%20pujas%20focus%20on%20themes%20of%20communal%20harmony%20and%20other%20socially%20progressive%20topics.%20In%20the%20background%20of%20this%20inter-communal%20amity%2C%20the%20replica%20of%20the%20upcoming%20Ram%20temple%20in%20Ayodhya%20being%20celebrated%20as%20a%20major%20puja%20destination%20in%20central%20Kolkata%20hits%20a%20highly%20dissonant%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20puja%20pandal%2C%20lit%20by%20psychedelic%20lights%20and%20lasers%2C%20has%20apparently%20been%20drawing%20record%20crowds%20from%20even%20before%20the%20pujas%20formally%20began%20on%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20October%2020.%20The%20puja%20is%20organised%20by%20Sajal%20Ghosh%2C%20a%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20councillor%20of%20the%20Kolkata%20Municipal%20Corporation%20(who%20is%20also%20the%20son%20of%20an%20ex-Congress%20leader%20who%20was%20the%20original%20organiser%20of%20the%20puja).%20Union%20home%20minister%20and%20BJP%20bigwig%20Amit%20Shah%20especially%20flew%20in%20from%20Delhi%20to%20inaugurate%20the%20pandal%20on%20October%2016.%20In%20his%20speech%20during%20the%20inauguration%2C%20he%20specifically%20mentioned%20that%20the%20puja%20pandal%20was%20a%20preview%20of%20the%20actual%20Ram%20temple%20coming%20up%20in%20Ayodhya.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Since%20then%2C%20along%20with%20thousands%20of%20people%2C%20a%20long%20lineup%20of%20BJP%20leaders%20including%20the%20Union%20education%20minister%20Dharmendra%20Pradhan%20and%20MP%20and%20head%20of%20the%20BJP%20youth%20wing%20Tejaswi%20Surya%20have%20visited%20the%20pandal.%20So%20have%20the%20governor%20of%20West%20Bengal%2C%20C.V.%20Ananda%20Bose%2C%20and%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20the%20Kolkata%20high%20court%2C%20Justice%20T.S.%20Sivagnanam.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20midst%20of%20this%20ostensible%20popularity%20and%20celebrity%20visits%2C%20what%20is%20lost%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20pandal%20celebrates%20a%20religious%20place%20that%20is%20being%20established%20upon%20the%20destruction%20of%20another%20place%20of%20worship.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fayodhyatimeline%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Babri%2520Masjid%2520is%2520constructed%2Cwas%2520the%2520birthplace%2520of%2520Rama.%5C%22%3EAyodhya%3A%20Once%20There%20Was%20A%20Mosque%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EForgotten%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20final%20construction%20of%20this%20temple%20is%20a%20culmination%20of%20a%20process%20marked%20by%20many%20years%20of%20communal%20discord%2C%20riots%2C%20loss%20of%20lives%20and%20the%20misery%20of%20people%20of%20both%20communities%20of%20Hindus%20and%20Muslims.%20That%20it%20finally%20marks%20the%20subjugation%20and%20disrespect%20of%20a%20religious%20community%20in%20a%20country%20constitutionally%20declared%20to%20be%20secular%20and%20democratic.%20It%20is%20true%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-ayodhya-verdict-possession%23%3A~%3Atext%3DNew%2520Delhi%253A%2520The%2520Supreme%2520Court%2527s%2Cwas%2520offered%2520in%2520the%2520mosque%5C%22%3Ein%20its%20verdict%20in%20November%202019%20handed%20over%20the%20disputed%20land%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20which%20the%20mosque%20once%20stood%20to%20the%20Hindu%20side%20for%20the%20construction%20of%20a%20temple.%20The%20court%20also%20ordered%20that%20a%20trust%20be%20formed%20by%20the%20government%20of%20India%20to%20which%20the%20land%20would%20be%20turned%20over%20and%20which%20would%20build%20the%20Ram%20temple%20on%20the%20land.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F02%2F21154340%2FBabri-Masjid-wikimedia.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-226304%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22351%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERear%20view%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20in%20Ayodhya%20before%20it%20was%20demolished.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMany%20people%20have%20questioned%20how%20the%20government%20of%20a%20constitutionally%20secular%20state%20can%20set%20up%20a%20trust%20which%20would%20build%20the%20place%20of%20worship%20of%20a%20particular%20religion.%20Irrespective%20of%20such%20questions%2C%20it%20is%20a%20fact%20that%20the%20court%20also%20ruled%20that%20the%20demolition%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20in%201992%20and%20the%20desecration%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20in%201949%20was%20in%20violation%20of%20law.%20Therefore%20it%20is%20now%20a%20matter%20of%20stated%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling%20that%20the%20temple%20in%20Ayodhya%20is%20being%20built%20upon%20the%20original%20foundation%20of%20events%20which%20are%20illegal.%20We%20know%20how%20the%20mandir-masjid%20dispute%20has%20been%20used%20over%20the%20last%20decades%20by%20a%20particular%20set%20of%20people%20and%20by%20a%20particular%20political%20party%20for%20gaining%20power%20and%20how%20the%20denouement%20of%20this%20dispute%20will%20be%20milked%20by%20the%20same%20set%20of%20people%20to%20continue%20to%20remain%20in%20power.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlthough%20it%20is%20widely%20represented%20as%20something%20representing%20the%20%E2%80%9Csentiment%E2%80%9D%20of%20Hindus%2C%20it%20is%20not%20something%20any%20right-thinking%20Hindu%20would%20be%20proud%20of.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20this%20backdrop%2C%20it%20is%20not%20surprising%20that%20a%20puja%20associated%20with%20a%20BJP%20leader%20would%20build%20a%20pandal%20representing%20the%20Ram%20temple%20in%20Ayodhya%2C%20especially%20as%20the%20BJP%20has%20not%20been%20able%20to%20make%20much%20inroads%20into%20the%20puja%20organising%20scenario%20of%20Kolkata%2C%20dominated%20by%20Trinamool%20Congress%20stalwarts.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20puja%20organised%20officially%20by%20the%20BJP%20at%20the%20Eastern%20Zonal%20Cultural%20Centre%20in%20Kolkata%20was%20a%20non-starter%20and%20was%20discontinued%20from%20this%20year.%20Except%20for%20some%20frivolous%20attempts%20by%20some%20Hindutva-affiliated%20organisations%20to%20organise%20pujas%20and%20draw%20some%20public%20attention%20(last%20year%20one%20such%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fat-hindu-mahasabha-durga-puja-a-mahishasur-which-looks-similar-to-mahatma-gandhi%5C%22%3Eattempt%20by%20the%20Hindu%20Mahasabha%20in%20Kolkata%20involved%20representing%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20as%20Mahishasura%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20had%20to%20be%20changed%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20pujas%20after%20a%20public%20outcry)%2C%20the%20RSS-BJP%20has%20not%20had%20much%20participation%20in%20the%20Durga%20Puja%20celebrations%20in%20Bengal.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETherefore%2C%20it%20is%20understandable%20that%20they%20have%20latched%20on%20to%20this%20puja%20pandal%20representing%20the%20Ram%20temple%20to%20show%20that%20they%20have%20arrived%20in%20the%20Durga%20Puja%20scenario%20and%20use%20it%20for%20further%20communal%20polarisation%20and%20political%20gain.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20is%20not%20understandable%20is%20why%20a%20single%20word%20is%20not%20being%20said%20by%20anyone%20%E2%80%93%20either%20the%20ruling%20Trinamool%20Congress%20or%20even%20the%20opposition%20CPI(M)%20and%20Congress%2C%20or%20the%20media%2C%20or%20the%20culturally%20sensitive%20intelligentsia%20of%20Bengal.%20No%20one%20has%20said%20yet%20that%20such%20a%20puja%20pandal%20actually%20goes%20completely%20against%20the%20traditions%20and%20the%20ethos%20of%20Durga%20Puja%20in%20Kolkata%2C%20which%20has%20always%20celebrated%20communal%20amity%20and%20friendship.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20pandal%20marking%20the%20subjugation%20and%20dishonour%20of%20a%20particular%20community%20cannot%20or%20should%20not%20be%20a%20centrepiece%20of%20the%20Durga%20Puja%20celebrations%20in%20Kolkata.%20There%20are%20multiple%20Durga%20Pujas%20in%20Kolkata%20which%20are%20organised%20jointly%20by%20Hindus%20and%20Muslims%2C%20there%20are%20even%20Durga%20Pujas%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Farticle%2Fsociety%2Fram-temple-ayodhya-khidirpur-muslims-durga-puja%3Futm%3Dauthorlistpage%5C%22%3Eheld%20in%20areas%20such%20as%20Khidirpur%20and%20Metiaburuj%20where%20the%20entire%20organising%20committee%20is%20Muslim%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHas%20anyone%20thought%20about%20what%20these%20organisers%20may%20be%20thinking%20of%20when%20they%20see%20lakhs%20of%20people%20visiting%20this%20pandal%20and%20the%20news%20reporters%20gushing%20on%20television%20about%20it%3F%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWill%20Muslim%20families%20who%20pandal%20hop%20in%20Kolkata%2C%20just%20like%20Hindu%20families%2C%20want%20to%20visit%20this%20pandal%20or%20are%20Muslims%20not%20welcome%20there%20at%20all%3F%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20a%20troubling%20sign%20of%20the%20times%20that%20mass%20sentiment%2C%20itself%20moulded%20carefully%20by%20propaganda%20in%20mainstream%20and%20social%20media%2C%20can%20wash%20away%20all%20conscientious%20thought%20and%20opinions.%20The%20reason%20why%20the%20TMC%2C%20CPI(M)%20and%20Congress%2C%20have%20remained%20silent%20about%20this%20travesty%20is%20that%20none%20of%20them%20would%20probably%20wish%20to%20alienate%20what%20they%20consider%20%E2%80%9CHindu%20voters%E2%80%9D.%20The%20intellectuals%20have%20kept%20quiet%20because%20no%20one%20wants%20to%20get%20into%20trouble.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%20one%20bothered%20when%20constitutional%20functionaries%20were%20visiting%20the%20pandal%20because%20it%20was%20considered%20to%20be%20a%20matter%20of%20personal%20faith.%20But%20it%20does%20not%20change%20the%20fact%20that%20such%20a%20celebration%20is%20in%20complete%20dissonance%20with%20what%20the%20Durga%20Puja%20festival%20in%20Bengal%20stands%20for.%20Unless%20acknowledged%20as%20such%2C%20it%20will%20open%20the%20floodgates%20for%20this%20very%20festival%20to%20be%20used%20for%20communal%20polarisation%20and%20destruction%20of%20communal%20harmony%20in%20Bengal.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPartho%20Sarothi%20Ray%C2%A0is%20an%20academic%20and%20activist.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697883810000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F18161334%2FScreenshot-2023-10-18-at-4.13.24%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fayodhya-ram-temple-durga-puja-kolkata%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Any%20pandal%20marking%20the%20subjugation%20and%20dishonour%20of%20a%20particular%20community%20goes%20against%20the%20very%20ethos%20of%20the%20festivities.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A129%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fayodhya-ram-temple-durga-puja-kolkata%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22IDBI%20Bank%20Q2%20results%3A%20Net%20profit%20jumps%2060%25%20to%20Rs%201%2C323%20cr%20on%20declining%20NPAs%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697882336000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2019-10%2F13%2Ffull%2F1570981965-7329.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fidbi-bank-q2-results-net-profit-jumps-60-to-rs-1-323-cr-on-declining-npas-123102100427_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20private%20sector%20lender%20controlled%20by%20India's%20largest%20insurer%20LIC%20had%20posted%20a%20net%20profit%20of%20Rs%20828%20crore%20in%20the%20year-ago%20period%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fidbi-bank-q2-results-net-profit-jumps-60-to-rs-1-323-cr-on-declining-npas-123102100427_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fidbi-bank-q2-results-net-profit-jumps-60-to-rs-1-323-cr-on-declining-npas-123102100427_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fidbi-bank-q2-results-net-profit-jumps-60-to-rs-1-323-cr-on-declining-npas-123102100427_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Manipur%20HC%20Allows%20Tribal%20Bodies%20to%20Appeal%20Against%20Controversial%20Order%20on%20ST%20Status%20for%20Meiteis%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F25174440%2Fimage-1084.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Manipur%20high%20court%20has%20allowed%20tribal%20bodies%20in%20the%20state%20to%20appeal%20against%20the%20controversial%20March%2027%20order%20that%20granted%20Scheduled%20Tribe%20(ST)%20status%20to%20Meiteis.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20order%20proved%20to%20be%20an%20immediate%20trigger%20plunging%20the%20state%20into%20a%20nearly%20five-month-long%20ethnic%20violence%2C%20starting%20on%20May%203.%20The%20court%20had%2C%20in%20its%20order%2C%20directed%20the%20state%20government%20to%20recommend%20ST%20status%20for%20Meiteis.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20October%2019%2C%20a%20division%20Bench%20of%20Justice%20Ahanthem%20Bimol%20Singh%20and%20Justice%20A.%20Guneshwar%20Sharma%20allowed%20tribal%20bodies%20to%20register%20their%20appeal%2C%20rejecting%20the%20pleas%20of%20the%20Manipur%20government%20and%20Meitei%20Tribes%20Union%20opposing%20the%20appeal.%20With%20the%20court%20now%20taking%20note%20of%20the%20grievances%20and%20arguments%20advanced%20by%20the%20tribal%20bodies%2C%20their%20appeal%20would%20be%20taken%20up%20for%20hearing%20in%20the%20coming%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20controversial%20order%20was%20passed%20by%20previous%20Acting%20Chief%20Justice%20M.V.%20Muralidharan.%20With%20the%20Union%20government%20now%20notifying%20Justice%20Muralidharan%E2%80%99s%20transfer%20to%20Calcutta%20high%20court%2C%20Manipur%E2%80%99s%20new%20Chief%20Justice%2C%20Justice%20Siddharth%20Mridul%2C%20is%20expected%20to%20take%20up%20the%20appeal%20for%20the%20hearing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20March%2027%20order%20became%20public%2C%20tribal%20bodies%20launched%20protests%20across%20the%20state%2C%20which%20soon%20turned%20into%20a%20never-ending%20ethnic%20conflict%20with%20a%20clear%20division%20between%20Meiteis%20on%20the%20one%20hand%20and%20Kukis%20on%20the%20other.%20The%20five-month-long%20violence%20has%20so%20far%20claimed%20180%20people%20and%20displaced%20lakhs%20of%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20violence%20began%20on%20May%203%2C%20various%20tribal%20bodies%2C%20led%20by%20the%20All%20Manipur%20Tribal%20Union%2C%20moved%20the%20Manipur%20high%20court%20seeking%20leave%20to%20file%20a%20third-party%20appeal%20against%20the%20controversial%20order%20as%20an%20aggrieved%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20on%20October%2017%2C%20the%20court%20acceded%20to%20their%20appeal.%20%E2%80%9CTaking%20into%20consideration%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20arguments%20advanced%20by%20the%20learned%20counsel%20appearing%20for%20the%20parties%20which%20needs%20to%20be%20examined%20and%20decided%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20materials%20available%20in%20the%20connected%20writ%20appeal%20and%20writ%20petition%20and%20taking%20into%20consideration%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20grievances%20raised%20by%20the%20applicants%2C%20we%20are%20inclined%20to%20grant%20leave%20sought%20by%20the%20applicants%20in%20the%20present%20application%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20said%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fmanipur-hc-allows-tribal-bodies-to-appeal-against-order-on-st-status-for-meiteis%2Farticle67442711.ece%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAppearing%20for%20tribal%20bodies%2C%20advocate%20Colin%20Gonsalves%20had%20faulted%20the%20controversial%20order%2C%20stating%20that%20Meiteis%E2%80%99%20claim%20to%20the%20ST%20status%20does%20not%20have%20merit%20and%20that%20the%20community%20has%20nowhere%20claimed%20to%20be%20backward%2C%20which%20is%20a%20prerequisite%20for%20claiming%20ST%20status.%20In%20their%20petition%2C%20the%20tribal%20bodies%20had%20also%20said%20that%20granting%20Meiteis%E2%80%99s%20ST%20status%20would%20mean%20snatching%20away%20the%20rights%20and%20benefits%20of%20existing%20STs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGonsalves%20had%20brought%20to%20the%20notice%20of%20the%20court%20that%20tribal%20bodies%20had%20not%20been%20given%20an%20opportunity%20to%20present%20their%20views%20before%20passing%20the%20March%2027%20order.%20Not%20allowing%20them%20to%20appeal%20the%20order%20would%20affect%20their%20rights%20as%20an%20aggrieved%20party%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Union%20government%20had%20raised%20no%20objections%20to%20allowing%20tribal%20bodies%20to%20appeal%20the%20order%2C%20the%20Biren%20Singh%20government%2C%20however%2C%20opposed%20the%20appeal%20against%20the%20order.%20The%20Singh%20government%2C%20like%20the%20Meitei%20Tribes%20Union%2C%20had%20said%20tribal%20unions%20cannot%20be%20considered%20as%20an%20%E2%80%9Caggrieved%20party%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20instant%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBesides%20this%2C%20Meitei%20Tribes%20Union%E2%80%99s%20review%20petition%20is%20also%20pending%20before%20the%20high%20court%2C%20where%20tribal%20bodies%20have%20also%20been%20made%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697881846000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F25174440%2Fimage-1084.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fmanipur-hc-allows-tribal-bodies-to-appeal-against-controversial-order-on-st-status-for-meiteis%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20order%20proved%20to%20be%20an%20immediate%20trigger%20plunging%20the%20state%20into%20a%20nearly%20five-month-long%20ethnic%20violence%2C%20starting%20on%20May%203.%20The%20court%20on%20March%2027%20directed%20the%20state%20government%20to%20recommend%20ST%20status%20for%20Meiteis.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fmanipur-hc-a